sourceDesc.p: The idea was to digitize the list of travels by Arthur Schnitzler that survives in his papers stored in the Cambridge University Library, folder A 175. The goal was not an edition of that list but to extract the information from the list and connect the timespans with geonames-IDs and locations. Therefore errors and mistakes of the list were changed without keeping track of the deleted information. Sometimes the diary was used to correct entries.
